Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.38,0:00:21.00,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take the sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.78,0:01:55.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're in the Zuland Plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:01:59.19,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, we should see it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.54,0:02:01.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.45,0:02:03.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! It's Mt. Fuji!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.61,0:02:05.39,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.54,0:02:07.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's the spirit mountain of Fuji!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.80,0:02:10.09,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It really is huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.09,0:02:11.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.05,0:02:12.97,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,There's something over there \Nthat looks like a cow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:15.03,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.28,0:02:18.94,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I think that's a green elk herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.94,0:02:20.30,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Are they dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.30,0:02:21.68,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.68,0:02:25.57,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,There's some distance between us, \Nand they're said to be calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:28.77,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They're so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.77,0:02:30.67,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They really look just like cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.04,0:02:33.64,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard they're delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.71,0:02:42.68,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1531,1)}The Midday Vampire
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.11,0:02:40.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Midday Vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.88,0:02:47.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The path here seems to be curving a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.39,0:02:49.67,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It runs along the coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.67,0:02:52.69,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,There's so much grass, \NI can't see the ocean at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.84,0:02:56.50,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But you can kind of smell the salt air, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.31,0:03:03.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure, honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.16,0:03:07.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, didn't Shiroe say this road was...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.48,0:03:09.56,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,The East Sea Road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.14,0:03:12.56,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's what this used to be called.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.44,0:03:15.60,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,It was one of the Five Routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.60,0:03:19.97,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,It began in Nihonbashi, Tokyo, and it \Nbecame an important trade route.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.69,0:03:25.64,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Today, the East Sea Road \Nis called "National Route 1,"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:27.33,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,and many roads branch off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.96,0:03:30.26,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,If you follow it all the way, \Nit'll take you to Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.26,0:03:31.06,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:33.96,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean Minami.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:37.12,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,So the roads are connected in this world, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.12,0:03:38.07,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.46,0:03:42.42,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,This might be the fastest route \Nto the Redstone Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.88,0:03:49.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I've never really thought about \Nthe roads that way before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.90,0:03:53.08,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Me, neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.08,0:03:55.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe is so amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.44,0:03:56.97,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,He knows so much stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.51,0:03:58.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.39,0:04:01.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,While I'm here, I'm gonna have an adventure, \Nand learn all kinds of things!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.00,0:04:06.35,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Think it's about time for lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.83,0:04:08.60,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.57,0:04:11.59,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.59,0:04:15.63,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The chief's ham sandwiches are so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.80,0:04:18.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No objection, whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.96,0:04:20.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:24.34,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Leave some for us, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:26.28,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:29.20,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:31.56,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost to Kalbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.56,0:04:32.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.51,0:04:33.59,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Stop there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.59,0:04:35.72,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.72,0:04:37.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The weather's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:41.16,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have Danish and Croissant \Nwork a little harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.45,0:04:45.74,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They're up for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.74,0:04:47.12,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We can keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:48.87,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.87,0:04:49.89,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.23,0:04:53.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The path opens before Rundel Haus Code!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.99,0:04:57.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's get going before it gets dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:04:58.80,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.48,0:05:13.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.54,0:05:17.48,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The time limit ran out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:19.55,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,For the Twin Horse Flute of Lyman!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.55,0:05:21.40,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:24.29,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It was six hours a day, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.33,0:05:30.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't anyone realize that, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.84,0:05:32.27,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.27,0:05:35.06,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Still, just because the time limit ran out,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they didn't have to run away so fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:39.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.80,0:05:43.32,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They ate carrots out of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.32,0:05:45.13,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They ate my cabbage, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.13,0:05:47.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They really have no sense of human gratitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:48.78,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they're horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:50.40,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Even horses...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:51.57,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Horses?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:55.13,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Then would they have horse gratitude, \Nrather than human gratitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:03.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The horses ran off, but this is kind of nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:03.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.23,0:06:06.80,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:10.83,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere between the \NKalbe Inn and Wilistoria Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.83,0:06:14.43,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Without them, we can't go on...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.88,0:06:18.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.79,0:06:21.08,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we'll just have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.08,0:06:23.44,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the cooking to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.44,0:06:26.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is where an adventurer really shines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:28.32,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Being an adventurer has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:30.23,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,We're camping out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.23,0:06:31.82,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.75,0:06:58.18,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:00.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.67,0:07:03.27,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.63,0:07:05.18,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.18,0:07:06.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The salt flavor is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.91,0:07:07.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:08.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.61,0:07:13.25,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:17.09,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm with Nyanta, I can make it just fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:18.70,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You just haven't practiced enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.70,0:07:19.75,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.24,0:07:24.85,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The chief would say, "You simply \Nneed to improve, little by little."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.85,0:07:26.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.45,0:07:28.51,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, Serara.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:32.01,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we had a cooking skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.60,0:07:35.64,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep relying on you, Serara!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:38.12,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.12,0:07:40.27,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I need to keep a hold of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.67,0:07:43.46,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I've got the Newlywed's Apron Dress, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.46,0:07:47.21,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I need to do my best for Nyanta \Nand for everyone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:55.78,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the next place we \Ncan stop is the town of Sazan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:57.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it take to get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.44,0:08:00.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,If we can only use the horses for six hours a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.70,0:08:02.86,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,it could take about three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.86,0:08:06.93,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this road so twisty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.93,0:08:09.76,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I wish it would just go straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:13.98,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but as long as I get to \Ntravel with everyone like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.98,0:08:16.01,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it takes a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:23.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I think Shiroe and the others sent us \Non this trip to teach us this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.26,0:08:25.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You're great, Minori.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.59,0:08:31.28,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like you've really grown up \Nfrom the person you used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:40.42,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Have I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:45.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd grown up with you, \Nbut I guess I have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:47.85,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.35,0:08:51.59,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.77,0:08:57.40,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I can do my best because you've always \Nbeen with me since I came to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.90,0:09:00.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm your big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:02.75,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.75,0:09:04.72,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm older!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.72,0:09:05.80,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.80,0:09:06.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.61,0:09:08.04,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm taller!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.04,0:09:09.82,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.01,0:09:16.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's been three days since they left on their trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:19.63,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they aren't getting homesick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.63,0:09:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.95,0:09:23.63,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they're having a great \Ntime, like it's a field trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.63,0:09:26.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They may be saying they don't want to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.45,0:09:29.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That would be a problem in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.60,0:09:33.94,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking pale again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.78,0:09:36.29,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:37.31,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.31,0:09:39.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're also glaring, Rieze.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.11,0:09:41.69,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You look just like my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.61,0:09:45.34,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:46.82,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.48,0:09:50.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is it hard without the scary glasses guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:52.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:55.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I realized how much I depended upon my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.64,0:09:58.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,For the moment, D.D.D. is stable,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.77,0:10:01.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,but we don't know what will happen in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.05,0:10:06.97,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I'm causing a lot of problems for people,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:08.66,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,and I will probably cause more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:11.24,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.28,0:10:15.15,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knows it's rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.15,0:10:18.81,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe will do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.83,0:10:22.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord won't think of it as a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.41,0:10:24.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He'll help you of his own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:26.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, so will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:27.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.61,0:10:30.55,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about us now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.14,0:10:32.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We're friends, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.72,0:10:37.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you laughing now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.50,0:10:40.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what being friends is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.03,0:10:41.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.03,0:10:49.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If we were in the old world, I'm sure \Nwe never could've been friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:53.00,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You might be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.63,0:10:54.40,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:10:56.51,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,that isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:10:59.77,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that the cute are drawn to one another!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.77,0:11:01.74,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I would've met you two, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:03.97,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Henrietta, stop rubbing your \Ncheek against mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.97,0:11:06.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't need that kind of assurance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:11.15,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:12.40,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.08,0:11:18.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a Teaching for a ninja \Nbody-swapping technique?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:21.81,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.63,0:11:32.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The sunset!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:34.79,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.79,0:11:36.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.35,0:11:37.63,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's the town of Sazan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.61,0:11:39.99,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.74,0:11:48.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Our musician says she'd like to play here tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.91,0:11:52.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We won't cause any trouble, so can \Nyou provide a place to perform?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.04,0:11:55.18,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,A forty-two, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.71,0:11:59.94,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But adventurer bards are pricey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.26,0:12:02.04,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need any payment!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.04,0:12:04.64,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll just let me play here, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:05.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.71,0:12:06.95,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.55,0:12:10.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Nice job, Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.12,0:12:13.35,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We get to perform, and we can \Nstay free for the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.28,0:12:17.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I am capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.33,0:12:22.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I'd like to say, but it's \Nthanks to Miss Isuzu's passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:23.88,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:26.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.38,0:12:29.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You guys perform to your hearts' content.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:31.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:35.73,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,I really have learned a lot on this journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.43,0:12:40.40,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,Even about the road we took to get here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.15,0:12:44.56,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered why there were \Nso many twists and turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.76,0:12:47.80,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,But when I traveled it on a carriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.80,0:12:49.93,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw that there were forests and hills,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.93,0:12:51.66,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,so we couldn't just go straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.62,0:12:56.17,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,The road goes around all those things \Nto make it easier for people and carriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:13:01.61,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,And this town was born so that, when you \Nstarted to feel tired, you could rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.74,0:13:05.18,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.29,0:13:10.79,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't be afraid of the boredom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:14.28,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's... Let's... Let's go outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.28,0:13:16.19,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,I think Rudy is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:20.21,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,When I wasn't able to play soccer with everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:23.29,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't just watch with an expression like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.29,0:13:30.55,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,Will my twisty path culminate in a city somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.17,0:13:34.70,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:37.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They loved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.04,0:13:39.53,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The customers kept asking for another song.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.53,0:13:41.70,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The encore calls wouldn't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.70,0:13:42.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.17,0:13:44.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:47.30,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:48.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They have a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.89,0:13:50.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Too much energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.65,0:13:52.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.77,0:13:54.43,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Are you curious, Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.04,0:13:56.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:14:00.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not such a boor as to be interested \Nin a secret chat among ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.21,0:14:06.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm simply impressed that they never \Nrun out of things to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.65,0:14:08.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's because they're girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.82,0:14:13.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Because they're girls... I mean, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.67,0:14:18.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then is the reason that Miss Isuzu is so \Npure and innocent because she's a lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.08,0:14:19.58,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:24.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,She always wants to hug me and rub my hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.66,0:14:28.72,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,I think she's just treating you like a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.50,0:14:32.88,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu doesn't act that way toward you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.19,0:14:35.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Does she simply not think I'm important?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.39,0:14:40.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't laugh, Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.52,0:14:41.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:44.01,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.01,0:14:47.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I think it might mean you're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.02,0:14:49.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Special?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.62,0:14:50.57,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.85,0:14:53.60,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Paw.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:57.27,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,You're my doggy, so you're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:01.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Why are you laughing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:06.25,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,When Isuzu thinks it's fun to be with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:08.09,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,that's what she does.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.45,0:15:10.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.18,0:15:11.09,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.48,0:15:14.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But I think that's different from \Nbeing especially beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.27,0:15:15.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,especially amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.86,0:15:19.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,or especially magnificently strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What does she think about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.20,0:15:24.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If thinking about it won't help,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.84,0:15:26.24,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,let's get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.24,0:15:27.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's not fair, Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.91,0:15:29.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get some sleep, too. Goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.91,0:15:34.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Goodnight, Rudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.10,0:15:42.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Today, we're going to cross into the Sakawa region.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.51,0:15:43.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sakawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:46.42,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,In the modern world, that's Odawara.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.42,0:15:48.35,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They're famous for their fish paste.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.35,0:15:49.88,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.40,0:15:53.64,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to follow this road \Nto the ruined castle of Ariba.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.29,0:15:56.58,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,To get to our goal, the Redstone Mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:16:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll either go off the Sea Road past the \NAriba ruins and onto a smaller road,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.89,0:16:04.63,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,or take a route that involves climbing mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:10.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Since this area is a rice paddy zone, \Nthere are nature-type monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.42,0:16:15.47,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Wild dogs, boars, and plant monsters \Nlive in the forests and mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.97,0:16:12.47,Monsters,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(251,1)\an9}Wild Dog \N Rank/ Field
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.34,0:16:15.11,Monsters,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(251,1)\an7}Boar (Mushroom) \NRank/ Field
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.47,0:16:18.16,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,but they keep to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.97,0:16:17.32,Monsters,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(251,1)\an7}Triffid \NRank/ Normal
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.75,0:16:24.94,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And Shiroe said the monsters along the road \Nhave their levels kept way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.12,0:16:29.45,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Then, even if we do run into one, we'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.45,0:16:31.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.68,0:16:33.54,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.54,0:16:35.03,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:39.74,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Will this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.20,0:16:42.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.45,0:16:45.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to have you take charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:48.42,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.42,0:16:51.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac's actually looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.73,0:16:53.57,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk like you know me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.13,0:16:56.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, so we have to train all the knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.97,0:16:59.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,How many levels should we raise them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.26,0:17:01.29,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Part of this is to forge friendships,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.29,0:17:03.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,so two or three is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.92,0:17:05.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't very greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:07.85,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.85,0:17:10.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be reckless with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:12.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.68,0:17:13.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you planning on power-leveling?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:20.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.97,0:17:24.98,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If we take the lead and fight high-level monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.98,0:17:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the lower-level guys will rise \Nin level automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.43,0:17:32.34,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Their levels will go up, \Nbut they won't get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.69,0:17:36.02,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You're so hard-headed, villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.02,0:17:38.62,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We can just alternate between \Npower-leveling and combat training.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.13,0:17:41.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll even focus on training!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:46.32,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is starting to sound really macho,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:47.62,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,but I guess it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.90,0:17:51.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Um, you still can't reach Crusty?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.90,0:17:52.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.87,0:17:54.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't responding on his Friend List, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.47,0:17:58.81,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing that's so important, \Nhe'd ignore his guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.20,0:18:00.52,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It could fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.07,0:18:05.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, lots of people are leaving D.D.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.58,0:18:07.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it's actually surprising
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the guild's managed to stay on course \Nfor these past three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.97,0:18:15.63,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried, villain?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.06,0:18:17.66,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Isaac?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.11,0:18:19.69,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.69,0:18:23.77,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He's either off playing somewhere or fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:28.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about D.D.D., but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.35,0:18:33.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The number of people in \NHonesty has exceeded 1,250.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:36.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is above our previous record.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.79,0:18:37.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.98,0:18:40.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The majority of the new \Nmembers are basically leechers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.03,0:18:44.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They don't hunt or gather outside of Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:48.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and they don't do crafting or \Ntrading in town, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.42,0:18:50.94,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Damned parasites.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.33,0:18:54.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There are people like that. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.63,0:18:58.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,These "people like that" are joining \Nour guild and taking it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.73,0:19:03.03,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,People in Akihabara and the guild \Nare getting angry with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.75,0:19:05.93,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of time \Nbefore that rage explodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.35,0:19:09.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I've shared our opinion \Nwith the Round Table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.40,0:19:11.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What can they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:13.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I think we simply have to kick them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:16.61,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Why not just limit who can join?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.61,0:19:18.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:21.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The only reason Honesty maintains its influence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.02,0:19:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and position on the Round Table
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is because we're the \Nthird-largest guild in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:32.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we lose that influence, we'll lose our \Nability to influence Akihabara politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:35.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I think it'd be healthier if the guild...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:39.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, the whole town of Akihabara went on a diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.22,0:19:51.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Those are cherry blossoms, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:53.00,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Nope...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.00,0:19:54.29,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They're plums.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.06,0:19:57.97,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They smell so nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.68,0:20:03.80,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A river!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.44,0:20:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.91,0:20:10.19,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This won't be easy to cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.59,0:20:12.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for a way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.07,0:20:17.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Save us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:24.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.79,0:20:26.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They're being chased by ogres!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.47,0:20:27.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Get over there and keep them safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.53,0:20:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.14,0:20:34.11,Monsters,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(215,1)}Man-Eating Demon \NRank/ Normal
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.97,0:20:34.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy levels are 21, 22, and 21!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:35.24,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.24,0:20:36.34,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.82,0:20:39.57,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:43.47,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Frost Spear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.83,0:20:53.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.36,0:20:54.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.22,0:20:56.65,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down! \NThere are fifteen adds!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.63,0:21:03.60,Monsters,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(215,1)}Nightshade Serpent \NRank/ Normal
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.78,0:21:00.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Nightshade Serpents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.55,0:21:02.75,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Their average level is 40!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.75,0:21:04.21,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And there are fifteen of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.21,0:21:05.99,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They're a spirit-type monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.99,0:21:08.29,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Dark spirits have either evil poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.29,0:21:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or resistance to mind attacks and insta-kills.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.11,0:21:16.05,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Not only might we get hurt, \Nbut the People of the Land could, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.87,0:21:17.54,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.58,0:21:21.80,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not even touching them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.99,0:21:25.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.64,0:21:34.89,Default - italics,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Servant Summon...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.41,0:21:36.89,Default - italics,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Wraith!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:57.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.96,0:22:07.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:09.85,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Roe 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.27,0:22:12.60,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,A summoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.35,0:22:20.01,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,A traveling vampire, heading south, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.83,0:22:21.36,HUD1,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(442,1)\an7}Roe 2 \N{\fs20}Race/ Half-Alv \NSummoner, Lv. 90 \NNo Guild
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.76,0:22:23.35,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A new person with glasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.98,0:22:29.45,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take the sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.51,0:24:08.07,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,"Call me 'big sister.'"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:12.70,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Roe 2, a mysterious big sister who takes \Njoy in being called "big sister."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.22,0:24:16.95,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya and the others enjoy their journey, \Neven with the chaos she causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.40,0:24:20.39,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,They encounter a group of adventurers who fight
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.39,0:24:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to protect People of the Land from monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.40,0:24:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Odyssey Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.40,0:24:30.99,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Odyssey Knights
